Text.Value: You are a warlock, are you not? You have a most powerful being at your back - and not counting Boo, there is also your patron!
You are a rogue, are you not? So while Minsc and Boo charge in front to do all of the work, you will creep behind the brain and stick it in its sticky parts!
Ah. Those are the strains of our little boat-ride, says Boo. But no matter - it is the smell of victory all the same!
I think you are thinking too much, my friend - that is why your brain-worm grows fat, while mine own withers from starvation.
Onward, then. If you are so set on taking the form of a fish, then Minsc and Boo will keep you from the Netherbrain's hook.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 131 - Waiting to choose a fate for Orpheus after dealing with Emperor

Text.Value: There, my friend. You ask if Minsc thinks this battle can be won?

EditorData.NodeContext: Holding back tears of inspiration at Boo's amazing end-game speech, which conveniently only he could understand.

Text.Value: *Dramatic squeaking!*
The illithid lied about his nether-pebbles. Only say the word, and Minsc will feed them to him.
You are a fighter, are you not? Master of combat - and this brain without even a set of fists to defend itself!
You are my friend still, and so honesty is owed. You. Are. Hideous.
You are a cleric, are you not? Ready to call upon the power of a guardian god, to spank this brain for bullying you!
You are a monk, are you not? Master of the mind - who better to bully the illithids on their own ground?!
You are a sorcerer, are you not? There is more magic in your blood than in all the brain's filthy fluids!
Leave.
If Karlach's mind is set, then Boo and I have faith. So bright a soul-fire cannot be quenched by any slippery fish-form.
You are a barbarian, are you not? The brain will wilt before our rage, and stain itself in its own fluids!
You are a ranger like Minsc, are you not? We have bested stranger beasts than this brain!
You are a wizard, are you not? And you mean to say you will let your brain be bested by this one?
Let us away, friend. Minsc and Boo are at your back. Your... slick and slippery back.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 112 - Orpheus Brain consumption / Turning into a mindflayer

Text.Value: The point is this. I still see the soul behind your eyes. And if you have taught me one thing, it is that all heroes need not look like Minsc.
Do you think we can win this?
Do you think we can win this?
But - if Minsc's words are not enough, then listen to those of one far wiser than he.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Takes Boo and presents him in-hand using same animations as Minsc_Recruitment.

Text.Value: You are a bard, are you not? Master of charms, and the only wit sharp enough to find rhymes for words such as 'courage', and 'victory', and 'Minsc'!
Back to the city - Boo thinks it is time for a second bite of this brain.
Minsc and Boo are honoured to be counted among them.
Your overripe melon-head, begging to be squashed. Your black and beady little eyes. Your - ! Yes, Boo, sorry.
That would be far too confusing for my hamster.
*Motivational squeaking!*
Minsc and Boo have no need of thinking. Minsc and Boo know.

EditorData.NodeContext: Fierce conviction, mirth at the fact that evil has no idea what's coming. (Interjections aside, possibly his last dialogue lines in the game)

Text.Value: You are a paladin, are you not? So full of yourself that there is more power in your promise than in all the brain's lumpy largeness!
You are a druid! With the might of hawk, and wolf, and hamster - all of which dine on brain, do they not?
*Heroic squeaking!*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Boo strikes a noble pose to give his speech.

Text.Value: The brain is near - can you smell it? Salt, and sweat, and - !
To take on the flayer-form... There must be another way to defeat the brain, surely? If not - better we fight on anyway, and die beautiful!
You have made some fine friends along your way. Each one a sword for the fight, a heart for your cause, and a boot for evil's underbelly!
How do you feel about me being a mind flayer now?

Synopsis:
The InParty for Minsc while in END_Main.
Morphic Pool (Arrival)
Astral Plane (Just after Netherbrain Confrontation)
Tadpole Choice (with Emperor in Astral Plane while making the choice to transform into a mind flayer)
High Hall Interior (after Astral Plane, views of Nautiloids, Dragons, and a city in ruin)
